(2743,1,'2024-04-08 09:28:26','2024-04-08 09:28:26','<!-- wp:montoya-gutenberg/container {\"background_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"type\":\"dark-section\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-montoya-gutenberg-container content-row dark-section normal\" data-bgcolor=\"#0c0c0c\" style=\"text-align:left\"><!-- wp:montoya-gutenberg/clipped-image {\"clipped_image\":\"https://kristar.show/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/main-hero.jpg\",\"clipped_image_id\":3108,\"clipped_image_alt\":\"KRISTAR\",\"clipped_video\":\"http://clapat.ro/themes/montoya/images/about.mp4\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-montoya-gutenberg-clipped-image clipped-image-wrapper\"><div class=\"clipped-image-pin\"><div class=\"clipped-image\"><img src=\"https://kristar.show/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/main-hero.jpg\" alt=\"KRISTAR\"/><div class=\"content-video-wrapper\"><video class=\"bgvid\" loop muted playsinline><source src=\"http://clapat.ro/themes/montoya/images/about.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\"/></video></div><div class=\"clipped-image-gradient\"></div></div></div><div class=\"clipped-image-content content-full-width\"></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:montoya-gutenberg/clipped-image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:montoya-gutenberg/container -->\n\n<!-- wp:montoya-gutenberg/container {\"padding_top\":\"yes\",\"padding_bottom\":\"yes\",\"change_header_color\":\"yes\",\"has_clip_path\":\"yes\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-montoya-gutenberg-container content-row light-section normal row_padding_top row_padding_bottom change-header-color has-clip-path\" data-bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" style=\"text-align:left\"><!-- wp:columns {\"className\":\"pinned-section\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns pinned-section\"><!-- wp:column {\"className\":\"pinned-element left\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column pinned-element left\"><!-- wp:heading {\"className\":\"big-title primary-font-title no-margins\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading big-title primary-font-title no-margins\">A Bubble. <br>A Story. <br>A Dream on Stage.</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column {\"className\":\"scrolling-element right\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column scrolling-element right\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>KRISTAR SHOW is more than a performance — it’s a world where bubbles tell stories, and children’s eyes light up with wonder. Founded by performer and mother Kristina in Miami, the show was born from a simple question: “What if bubbles could carry a story?”<br>What started in 2013 as a birthday party act grew into something much more — a theatrical journey filled with music, imagination, and thousands of shimmering spheres.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Our Mission<br></strong>To create unforgettable, interactive, and visually stunning theatrical shows for children and families — combining the playfulness of bubbles with the heart of storytelling.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What We Believe</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Children deserve theater made just for them<br>Our shows are crafted with love, laughter, and just the right amount of magic — perfect for kids aged 2+ and their grown-ups.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Parents should enjoy it too<br>We build stories that are meaningful and joyful for the whole family, not just the little ones.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Every venue matters<br>Whether it’s a grand theater or a cozy school stage, we treat every space like Broadway — with professionalism, care, and respect.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Safety is not optional<br>Our bubble formula is eco-friendly, chemical-free, and 100% safe for kids, performers, and stage equipment.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Meet Kristina — Creator &amp; Lead Performer<br></strong>Kristina is a lifelong artist, educator, and performer. After years of delighting private audiences with her interactive Bubble Show, she envisioned a new type of family theater — one that combines storytelling, visuals, and sensory magic. Her dream became KRISTAR SHOW, and now she brings that dream to life on stage for families across the U.S.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Where We Perform</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Theaters</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Schools</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Cultural centers</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Family festivals</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Community events</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>From Miami to New York — and soon, to your city.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A Message from Kristina:<br>“<em>When I step on stage and see a child’s face light up — that’s when I know we’ve created something special. KRISTAR SHOW is about joy, imagination, and bringing families together through wonder.</em>”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let’s bring the magic to your stage!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns --></div>\n<!-- /wp:montoya-gutenberg/container -->\n\n<!-- wp:montoya-gutenberg/container {\"background_color\":\"#0c0c0c\",\"type\":\"dark-section\",\"padding_top\":\"yes\",\"alignment\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-montoya-gutenberg-container content-row dark-section normal row_padding_top\" data-bgcolor=\"#0c0c0c\" style=\"text-align:center\"><!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:montoya-gutenberg/icon-box {\"icon\":\"fa fa-paper-plane fa-2x\",\"title\":\"Email\",\"type\":\"block-boxes\",\"co